## 5. Section 2 — 12-Month Reference Strip

A compact, collapsible reference panel positioned between the page header and the capability grid. It is collapsed by default — the user can expand it if they want to reference the synthesis while making selections.

**Collapsed state:**
- A single line: `Q1 synthesis context — your 12-month focus areas and sequencing insight`
- An expand chevron on the right

**Expanded state:**
Three compact callout items pulled directly from the Roadmap Review 12-month accordion:

| Item | Label | Content |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `LOAD-BEARING AREAS` | The 2-3 capability areas identified as highest structural leverage for this year — named, one sentence each |
| 2 | `DEPENDENCY CHAIN` | The sequencing insight from the 12-month synthesis — what unlocks what |
| 3 | `PRIMARY CONSTRAINT` | The single thing most likely to slow progress — framed as context, not warning |

This panel is read-only. It is a reference layer, not an introduction. The user has already read this content in the Roadmap Review — it is surfaced here only to keep the strategic logic accessible while they work.

Visual treatment: subtle background fill, slightly compressed type, clearly secondary to the capability grid below. Does not dominate the screen.

