## 7. Section 4 — 3P Commitment Columns

### 7.1 Layout

Three equal-width columns sitting below the capability grid, spanning the full page width. Each column holds exactly 3 capability selections — no more, no less. The 9/9 total is enforced: the Lock & Proceed button remains disabled until all three columns have exactly 3 selections each.

**Column headers:**

| Column | Label | Subtitle |
|---|---|---|
| Prioritize | `Prioritize` | `Core focus this quarter` |
| Plant | `Plant` | `Prepare for next horizon` |
| Iterate | `Progressively Iterate` | `Maintain and refine` |

**Column color coding:** Keep the existing color treatment — blue for Prioritize, green for Plant, orange for Iterate. This is already established in the wireframe and should not change.

### 7.2 Adding Capabilities to Columns

Two interaction methods — both must work:

**Drag and drop:** Drag a card from the grid and drop it into a column slot.

**Click to add:** Click the `+` button on a grid card — this opens a simple column picker: three buttons labeled Prioritize / Plant / Iterate. Selecting one places the card in that column. This is the primary interaction for users who find drag-and-drop cumbersome.

### 7.3 Column Card — Display

Once a capability is placed in a column, its column card displays:

| Element | Content |
|---|---|
| Category tag | Dimension label in dimension color |
| Capability name | Full name |
| Maturity score | Percentage |
| Stage status badge | Below Stage / At Stage / Ahead of Stage |
| Remove control | `×` icon — returns the card to the unselected state in the grid |
| Move control | A subtle drag handle or `Move` link — allows repositioning between columns without removing |

### 7.4 Selection Counter

A persistent bottom bar (or sticky footer) displays the current selection count:

`Selection: 3/3 Prioritize · 2/3 Plant · 1/3 Iterate — 6 of 9 selected`

This updates in real time as cards are added or removed. When 9/9 is reached: `Selection Complete (9/9) — Ready to lock your Q1 focus.` The Lock & Proceed button activates.

### 7.5 Parking Lot (Future Quarters)

A fourth column — visually de-emphasized, positioned to the right of the three active columns or accessible via a tab — labeled `Parked for Later`. No slot limit. Cards placed here are saved as deferred — not part of the active quarter, not forgotten. No further interaction required on this screen for parked items.

