## 12. Tone & Language Principles

All platform-generated content — expanded view text, reference strip content, completion synthesis — must follow:

- **Observational, not prescriptive** — the platform reveals what things imply, never tells the founder what to do
- **Stage-calibrated** — all language references the user's specific stage by name
- **Specific** — references real capability names and real dimension names, never generic business language
- **Non-evaluative** — the platform does not judge selections as good or bad, right or wrong
- **Peer-level** — strategic advisor voice, not coach or educator

